Package pathfinder.textInterface

Class TextInterfaceController

  • java.lang.Object
    • pathfinder.textInterface.TextInterfaceController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InputHandler
    public class TextInterfaceController
extends java.lang.Object
implements InputHandler
    This class does most of the controller work for the text user interface version of the pathfinder application. It does things like decide how to respond to input, communicate requests for information or computation to the Model, instruct the View on how to respond, and pass information from the Model to the View.

    • Method Detail

      • launchApplication

        public void launchApplication()
        Begins the application by displaying some basic information and prompting the user for the starting command.

        On normal operation, this method does not return until the application is being shut down. Calling this method transfers control of the current thread to the provided TextInterfaceView.

      • handleInput

        public void handleInput​(java.lang.String input)
        Responds to user commands based on the text of the command. Echoes blank commands and lines beginning with "#" to the standard output.
        Specified by:
        handleInput in interface InputHandler
        Parameters:
        input - The text command entered by the user.
